x4freetext: An isotopically enriched 208Pb
target with thickness of about 120 ug/cm2 on a 20
ug/cm2 12C backing.
Two Si-detector telescopes
were fixed at the backward angle regions, with
angular coverages of 99-127 deg and 144-171 deg. Each
telescope contains three layers of Si detectors, a 20
um single-side strip detector (16 channels) with an
active area of 50 x 50 mm2 as the Delta-E detector, a
60 um double-side strip detector (16 x 16 pixels) and
a 1 mm quadrant silicon detector with the same areas
as the residual energy (ER) detectors.
An array including eight silicon PIN-diode
detectors with a coverage from 20-68 deg to measure
the elastic scattering. Two additional PIN detectors
were placed at +-15 deg as monitors, used for the
data normalization.
